.\" SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-2-Clause
.Dd May 2, 2026
.Dt GETRLIMITS 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm getrlimit
.Nd print resource limit names and values
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl n
.Op Ar rlimit ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility prints resource limit constants and their current soft and hard
limits as returned by
.Xr getrlimit 2 .
.Pp
If no operands are given, all known resource limits are printed.
.Pp
Each operand is either a numeric resource limit code or a symbolic resource
limit name.
Symbolic names may be provided with or without the
.Dq RLIMIT_
prefix.
.Pp
Unless
.Fl n
is specified, output consists of four tab-separated fields:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "hard-limit" -compact
.It name
The symbolic resource limit name.
.It soft-limit
The current soft limit.
.It hard-limit
The current hard limit.
.El
.Pp
A limit value equal to
.Dv RLIM_INFINITY
is printed as
.Dq infinity .
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl n
Print only the symbolic name of each matching resource limit, omitting the
numeric code and limit values.
.El
.Sh OPERANDS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ar rlimit
A numeric resource limit code, such as 7, or a symbolic name such as
.Dq RLIMIT_NOFILE
or simply
.Dq NOFILE .
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std getrlimit
.Sh EXAMPLES
Print all known resource limits:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ getrlimit
.Ed
.Pp
Print the current soft and hard open file limits:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ getrlimit NOFILE
.Ed
.Pp
Print only the symbolic names of all known resource limits:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ getrlimit -n
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr prlimit 1 ,
.Xr prlimit 2 ,
.Xr getrlimit 2 ,
.Xr setrlimit 2
.Sh STANDARDS
Resource limit constants are system-dependent and are commonly defined in
.In sys/resource.h .
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Ricardo Branco
